Finally, terminal monohydroxy groups of PEG-DTPA were used to end-cap precursor copolymer once more with PPTS (1%) catalysis to generate the final block copolymer composition (Fig. 3
                        ). The desired product (in. 80% yield) was purified and investigated by proton NMR (Fig. 2S a&b). The FT-IR spectrum of PM is shown in Fig. 4
                        a. The characteristic peaks of the synthesized micelles at 3268 (broad), 2909, and 1719 cm−1 are assigned to the formation of hydroxyl, alkenyl C–H, and carbonyl products, respectively [44]. As well, there was an obvious variation of the spectrum at 1000–1150 cm−1 given to the ether C–O–C stretching, overlapping with the cleavage of the acetal O–C–O bonds.

DOX release from NCD@DOX/PM in pH 5.0 first exhibited an immediate release during the former 8 h and then a continual release for the rest (Fig. 7). Different kinetic models were evaluated to find out the mechanism of drug release from the designed carrier. As shown in Fig. 8
                        , the release curves were fitted to four diverse models to conclude which one showed the maximum linear relationship with empirical data (Table 1
                        ).
